<TITLE> 25 injured in Dinajpur train collision </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dinajpur, Apr 4 (bdnews24.com) - At least 25 people sustained injuries in a head-on collision between two trains Saturday afternoon at the entrance of Parbartypur Railway Station in Dinajpur. The accident occurred as a local train entered the station without the proper signal at 5.20pm and hit the intercity Rupsha Express waiting at Level Crossing-1, said assistant station master Nurul Amin. Local train driver Bazlur Rahman and assistant Horen Chandra were suspended, director general of railways Belayet Hossain told bdnews24.com. Bazlur Rahman, however, claimed he entered the station on a signal. A five-member probe committee has already been formed, he said. Trains were held up for over four hours on the route, resuming at 9:40 after rescue workers from Lalmonirhat removed the trains and repaired the line, Nurul Amin told bdnews24.com at around 9:45pm. "Train movements can not come to normalcy before 11pm. Ekata, Rupsha and Nil Sagor came to a halt due to the accident," Mushfiqur Rahman, general manager of Western Zone of Bangladesh Railway. The local train--Down Local Train-438 was coming from Birol in the district and Rupsha Express was heading for Chilahatti in Nilphamari, Nurul Amin said. Among the injured, two including driver Bazlur Rahman, were admitted to Parbartypur Railway Hospital. Others received first aid at the Upazila Health Complex. Most of the passengers were hurt as they jumped out of the train to escape the collision, said Amin. bdnews24.co
